@Anonsen
You just have to transfer the files to Fat32 partition of your harddisk and Wii-Flow loads it. it is so much better to use wbfs then .iso files. So much less activity on harddisk and saves the much needed space bcoz i dont need much larger hdd anyways.

Also, you can just use your friends pc and by using wii-backup-manager transfer the files to harddisk.
